 or in the case of a smallish guild or a non-guilded cleric (heaven forbid) friends of the cleric.  <br><br>Meaning that a guildee or friend of the cleric in line can /tell the other peeps in line or OOC 'I am taking over the camping spot of So and So cleric for awhile' and so forth.  That way you can rotate guildees in and out and break the camp up in shifts.  Each guildee can take a four hour window or such and it would make the RF camp much easier.  That way the Cleric doesn't have to take 20-25 days out of their schedule.<br><br>This only applies to the Clerics in line for a spot at RF, NOT the Cleric who is currently camping RF.  When your spot comes up and you inherit the RF camp, then the same gentlemen agreement that is in place now becomes in play.<br><br>I think it behooves us all as a server to try to come up with the easiest, smoothest, and best way to camp RF.<br><br>This is just one suggestion. <br><br>Sandalorn Ellesarien<br>Far Seekers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uloadeenngplezewayt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loadeenng Plezewayt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tad-pole</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/5/02 1:12:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1183.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ragefire Question/Suggestion</span><hr size=1> /yawn ragefire will be the same as it has always been, you want the camp, you sit there until the cleric that is already there leaves <p>"No, we never talk to consumers – they just fuck us up. Someone asked for a copy of our market research which made us take the decision to do EverQuest. I said we hadn't done any market research. Had we done, the game would never have been made. We never focus on them. Gamers don't know what they