 have gotten many letters and petitions about Ragefire as of late, and as such have made the following changes to the spawn and the quest. <br><br>The biggest complaint that people had was that he was always permanently camped with 2 or 3 clerics waiting on the spawn. To counteract this, we have added more mobs that now drop the unpure heart of Zordak Ragefire. Those mobs are as follows: One random moss snake every 10,000,000 game days; A spawned version of Ragefire on the 7th island in sky (the quest NPC is on a 3-7 day timer, and requires that all mobs from island 4 to 7 be down before he will pop); and finally, the heart now drops off Vulak as well. Due to the farmable nature of this spawn, we have also removed all of Vulak's other drops, so people won't want to kill him for items *other* than the heart. <br><br>The next biggest complaint about the camp was that it was upwards of 6 days that require constant camping in skyfire. <br><br>After a long debate, we decided the best way to deal with this problem was a good dose of &quot;things could be worse if you think about it&quot;. <br><br>To illustrate: Ragefire is now a random spawn in *every* zone. There can be only one up at a time, and should he not be engaged within 1 hour of his pop time, he despawns for a period of 3 to 21 days. He has a 50% chance of spawning in the zone that is actually the little box with locations written on the walls that no one knows how to get into or out of without GM assistance. The other 50% of the time is broken up into equal chances to spawn in Veeshans Peak, Under the world in the dreadlands, Chardok in the queen's room, Crushbone RoF (not yet patched to live servers), Forta Knoxa (Legends server only) and CShome. We have been assured that at least the spawn in CShome is accessable, all our guides and GM's have seen it first hand, so we don't know what the fuss is about. <br><br>Finally, after many complaints from the Necromancer community about the functionality of their epic, we've decided to replace the effect of the cleric epic, Rivivesence, with the effect on the necro epic. Now that they share the same ability, we are confident that the utility of the necromancer epic will rise: after all, it's as good as a cleric epic now. <br><br>Thanks very much,<br>Someguyat Verantwhodoesn'tknowmuch<br><br>PS:<br>Guide Soandso here. I am afraid that we have to remove your last name, of Verantwhodoesn'tknowmuch as it contains an improper character. In this case, the apostrophe stands for the &quot;o&quot; in does nOt. We have to remove the last name. Please choose another now. <br><br>Very well, your last name of tackedmymanhood has been approved, as it does not obviously contain any words or phrases. <br><br>Yers,<br> <p><font color="blue">Roggulbuk Bonesmasher</font><br><b><i><font color="Orange">Myrama...Mirda..Murma... WARRIOR, 57</font></i></b><br><font color="black">An Cat Dubh</font><br>Me Mudders Yungust Son<br>Less babies, mor fibur!!<br><a href="http://www.clanbashemded.com"><img src="http://www.clanbashemded.com/images/clan2.jpg" width="208" height="45" border="0"></a><br><a href=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44431"><font color="yellow">Shinies</font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umavier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mavier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wog</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/8/02 1:13:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1183.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ragefire Question/Suggestion</span><hr size=1> See I feel better about camping RF as he is now already :) <p>Balme<BR>57th Cleric<BR><BR>Empire of the Forgotten<BR><BR>Mavier Ombracavaliere<BR>51st Shadow Knight<BR><BR><embed src="